[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

The \H and \S suits look really good, but neither of them are 5 cards, so you open 1\C. Partner responds 1\H. What is your next bid? 

Partner's bid shows 6-10 points and at least 4 \Hs. Since you now know there is an 8-card Major suit fit you revalue your hand, adding 2 more points for the singleton \D.

That gives you 20 points; add partner's 6-10 and you have enough for game. She who knows, goes, so you bid 4\H.}

